## Session 51 — Completeness verify endpoint hardening (timeout, CORS, WS URL, state reset)

| id | Feature | Status | Source | Acceptance |
|----|---------|--------|--------|------------|
| F-178 | **Completeness verify endpoint hardening (Session 51).** Eight bugs fixed after the F-177 feature shipped: (1) `/api/v1` prefix missing in `lib/api/m1-completeness.ts` (3 URLs) → 404; (2) `httpx.ReadTimeout` on slow upstream → `httpx.Timeout(connect=10/read=120/write=10/pool=10)` + `_HTTP_RETRY_ATTEMPTS=2` retry-on-Timeout loop; (3) 500 without CORS headers (Starlette `ServerErrorMiddleware` sits above CORS) → catch-all `except Exception` in `_run_verify` raising `HTTPException(500, detail=f"Verification failed: {type(exc).__name__}: {first_line[:240]}")` plus `httpx.TimeoutException → 504` and `httpx.HTTPError → 502`; (4) WS dialled `ws://window.location.host` (Next dev port) → `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` + `.replace(/^http/i,"ws")`; (5) WS reconnect storm → backend sends `{type:"done", terminal:true}` then `ws.close(code=1000)`; client respects either signal; (6) `AttributeError: 'URL' object has no attribute 'human_repr'` (httpx<0.27) → `resp.url.human_repr()` → `str(resp.url)`; (7) uvicorn dead between bugs → venv-activation recommended; (8) panel stale state on `taskId` switch → `useEffect([taskId])` resets `result`/`refetchResult`/`autoRan`. Belt-and-braces approach on WS termination + python-atomic-write protocol throughout. | 🟢 | session 51 (user-reported issues during integration of F-177) | (1) Verify on slow upstream completes within ~120s + retry, returns either result or clean 504 with CORS headers; (2) WebSocket connects once on terminal task, closes cleanly with code 1000, client stops trying; (3) switching historical runs shows fresh panel state immediately; (4) unexpected exceptions surface as `Verification failed: <ExceptionClass>: <msg>` in panel; (5) all 4 tracker files reference Session 51 / F-178. |

