| F-177 | **Completeness check + re-fetch + spider EN→SI→TA fallback (Session 50).** User manually compared website list vs DB across two months — found 12% miss rate Feb 2026 (25 of 207) and 40% miss rate Jan 2026 (103 of 260, including 10-day Jan 19–28 blackout). Separately the spider silently dropped Sinhala/Tamil-only gazettes. Planning questions confirmed: fallback EN→SI→TA (no schema change), manual + auto verify, table with per-row + bulk re-fetch, "unparsed" pills. New backend service `app/services/m1_completeness_check.py` (265 lines, httpx + lxml listing diff). New endpoints module `app/api/v1/m1_completeness.py` (382 lines, three routes: `POST /verify/{task_id}`, `POST /verify`, `POST /refetch-missing`; Pydantic schemas `MissingItemOut`/`VerifyResultOut`/`VerifyByScopeIn`/`RefetchMissingIn`/`RefetchOneOut`/`RefetchMissingOut`; refetch mirrors `M1RegulationsInsertPipeline._insert_rows` then enqueues `extract_gazette.delay(...)`). Registered under `prefix="/admin/m1/extraction"`. Frontend `lib/api/m1-completeness.ts` typed client + `components/m1-extraction/missing-gazettes-panel.tsx` (372 lines, auto-trigger on terminal + manual button + table with `unparsed` pills + per-row & bulk re-fetch + refetch summary). Wired into source extraction page above `<ExtractionSummaryCard>`. Spider `gazette_spider.py` rewritten with `_LANG_PRIORITY = {"en":0,"si":1,"ta":2}` + `_language_for(url)` helper + `best_by_number` buffer-then-pick → one yield per gazette. | 🟢 | session 50 (user: "find them and fix them … check them and for the … chanegs also upgrade them") | (1) Click "Verify completeness" on a healthy upstream returns missing items within ~5s; (2) per-row "Re-fetch" inserts new `m1_regulations` + `m1_gazette_items` rows, enqueues `extract_gazette`, returns one of `queued`/`duplicate`/`missing_download_url`/`error`; (3) bulk "Re-fetch all" equivalent for all items with `download_url`; (4) spider ingests Sinhala-only / Tamil-only gazettes that were previously dropped, English-priority preserved when all three exist; (5) Session-23 integration test still passes; (6) all 4 tracker files reference Session 50 / F-177. |

