| F-175 | **Live count polling for `summaryForResume` (Session 49).** Page-level `summaryForResume` react-query had `staleTime: 8_000` but no `refetchInterval` — once spider's Celery task hit SUCCESS counts froze at "100 extracted · 0 preprocessed" even while extract_gazette + preprocess_gazette were still processing 100+ PDFs (manual reload was needed). Added `refetchInterval` callback that polls every 5s while any row is in flight; stops automatically when `ingested === 0 && extracted === 0 && preprocessed + extraction_failed >= in_scope`. Polling is opt-in per query so other panels stay unaffected. Page edit via python-atomic-write per Session-48 protocol. | 🟢 | session 49 (user: "when extraction started its crawling and extracting but in the frontend its not updated in real time when after reload its showing updated") | (1) After Celery SUCCESS, counts continue to update every 5s without manual reload; (2) polling stops once `ingested + extracted == 0` AND `preprocessed + failed >= in_scope`; (3) `PipelineRunStatusCard` phase derivation now reflects accurate counts live. |
| F-176 | **`SpiderResultCard` polished display (Session 49).** Replaced raw `<pre>{JSON.stringify(status.data.result, null, 2)}</pre>` block on source extraction page with new `components/m1-extraction/spider-result-card.tsx` (196 lines): status pill (Success/Failed driven by `status === "ok" && returncode === "0"`), 2×2 labelled grid (Source mono chip / Spider mono / Scope parsed `YYYY-MM-DD..YYYY-MM-DD` → `Date.toLocaleDateString` per locale / Return code), "Other fields" fallthrough for forward-compatibility with future backend keys. Works for every source (EGZ/GZ/BILL/ACT) because the route is shared. | 🟢 | session 49 (user: "in beautiful display the {…} in all the sources of extraction") | (1) Spider result rendered as polished card on all four source pages; (2) success → green pill + green border-left; non-zero returncode → red Failed pill + red border-left; (3) parsed scope reads "1 Feb 2026 → 28 Feb 2026" via locale; (4) unknown future fields appear under "Other fields" mono list. |

## Session 48 — Vault recovery from Write-tool truncation + backend IndentationError + NUL bytes

| id | Feature | Status | Source | Acceptance |
|----|---------|--------|--------|------------|
| F-178 | **Vault recovery from Write-tool truncation + extract_gazette IndentationError + 755 NUL bytes (Session 48 incident).** `npm run build` reported walls of TS17008 / TS1005 / TS1010 / TS1002 errors. Hex dumps revealed mid-content truncation across 13 frontend files (`providers.tsx` 16 lines mid-comment; `next.config.mjs` 15 lines ending `swcMinify: t`; dashboard 359 lines mid-string; login 192 lines mid-className; sidebar 899 of 960; etc). Write/Edit tools had returned "file created successfully" on every truncating call. Backend `extract_gazette.py` had 755 trailing NUL bytes + IndentationError at line 212 (misplaced `_emit` block at wrong indent). Recovery: (1) emitted PowerShell `git restore` command for 13 frontend files; (2) removed misplaced `_emit` block at lines 200-211 in `extract_gazette.py`; stripped 755 NUL bytes via `data.rstrip(b'\x00').rstrip()` (15193 bytes, ends `    return body\n`); confirmed `ast.parse` clean; (3) swept sibling backend/ML files — all 0 nulls; (4) adopted python-atomic-write protocol for files >~25KB with verify-after-write (`wc -l` + `tail -3` + null-byte check + `ast.parse` for Python). Pattern of truncation correlates strongly with long writes containing em-dashes / special quotes / emoji. Separately user hit `ModuleNotFoundError: fastapi` running uvicorn from `/usr/lib/python3.14` (system Python) — pointed at `source /mnt/c/Reasearch/xyz/.venv/bin/activate && uvicorn app.main:app --reload`. | 🟢 | session 48 (npm build failure cascade + user-reported "ModuleNotFoundError") | (1) All 13 frontend files restored via `git restore`; `git status` clean for those paths; (2) `python3 -c "import ast; ast.parse(open('extract_gazette.py').read())"` exits 0; (3) sibling backend/ML files report 0 NUL bytes; (4) python-atomic-write protocol adopted for the remainder of the session; (5) Session-48 entry in SETUP_COVERAGE.md documents the Edit-tool truncation policy. |

## Session 47 — Frontend perf overhaul (dashboard streaming + login handoff + bundle/query tuning + recharts code-split)

| id | Feature | Status | Source | Acceptance |
|----|---------|--------|--------|------------|
| F-174 | **Frontend perf overhaul (Session 47).** User reported >10s login → dashboard delay. Three compounding causes: (1) login handler 4 sequential calls (`AuthApi.login()` → `/api/auth/establish` → `/api/auth/me` → `router.replace()` → `router.refresh()`); (2) dashboard server component awaited `Promise.all` of 5 backend fetches before returning any HTML; (3) react-query `refetchOnWindowFocus/Reconnect/Mount: true` caused redundant fetches per navigation. Rewrote dashboard with Suspense streaming (synchronous shell + 3 async subsections each in `<Suspense>`). `/api/auth/establish` now base64url-decodes JWT payload + returns role inline; login page drops `/me` and `router.refresh()`. `next.config.mjs` adds `productionBrowserSourceMaps:false / swcMinify:true / compress:true / output:"standalone" / poweredByHeader:false` + expanded `optimizePackageImports` (lucide-react/date-fns/recharts/framer-motion/6 @radix-ui/*) + AVIF/WebP images config with `documents.gov.lk` + `enigmatrix-backend.vercel.app` `remotePatterns`. QueryClient defaults: `staleTime: 60_000 / gcTime: 10*60_000 / refetchOn*: false / retry:1 / retryDelay:1_000`; mutations `retry:0`. Recharts components in `m1/pipeline/page.tsx` wrapped in `next/dynamic({ssr:false, loading: () => <Skeleton/>})`. Build collision `import dynamic from "next/dynamic"` vs `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"` → renamed to `nextDynamic`. | 🟢 | session 47 (user: "when logged in getting more than 10sec to goes to the dashboard") | (1) Login → dashboard shell paint < 1s; (2) login network sequence reduced from 4 calls to 2 (no `/me`, no `refresh`); (3) back-navigation pops instantly from react-query cache; (4) m1 pipeline page first interactive paint faster (recharts deferred); (5) all 4 tracker files reference Session 47 / F-174. |

