| F-173 | **Extraction running UX upgrade (Session 46).** User reported page said "Completed SUCCESS" while 2 rows still at `ingested` and 154 not yet preprocessed. Planning questions confirmed all three detail levels (per-step + per-PDF + sub-step), WebSocket transport, end-to-end completion, work across frontend + backend + ML. New frontend `components/m1-extraction/pipeline-run-status-card.tsx` (481 lines, exports `derivePipelinePhase(celeryStatus, counts)` returning one of 7 phases; three-phase tracker; live sub-step pill). New frontend `lib/hooks/useExtractionLiveFeed.ts` (141 lines, WebSocket client with exponential backoff 1s → 30s). Wired both into source extraction page replacing single-line Celery banner. New ML `enigmatrix-ml/m1/extraction/progress.py` (114 lines, canonical `ExtractionPhase` literal: `classifying | extracting_text | ocr | language_detection | wijesekara | preprocessing | indexing`; `PHASE_LABELS` dict; `emit(cb, ...)` helper). Re-exported from ML `__init__.py`: `PHASE_LABELS`, `ExtractionPhase`, `ProgressCallback`, `SubStepEvent`, `emit_progress`. New backend `app/services/m1_extraction_live_feed.py` (84 lines, sync `redis-py` publisher reusing `CELERY_BROKER_URL`). Modified `app/tasks/m1/extract_gazette.py` — `_emit(task_self, ...)` helper calls `self.update_state(state="PROGRESS", meta=payload)` AND `publish_substep(...)`; plumbed `task_self` through `_extract_gazette_async` → `_extract_gazette_body`; hooked at three phase boundaries (classify, extract/OCR, indexing). New backend `app/api/v1/m1_extraction_ws.py` (180 lines, FastAPI `@router.websocket("/extraction/{task_id}")` with token query-param auth via `decode_token(token, expected_kind="access")`; subscribes to source-scoped Redis pub/sub channel; three concurrent loops: pubsub pump / 25s heartbeat / 2s Celery terminal watcher). Registered WS router in `app/api/v1/router.py`. Source-scoped pub/sub channel is a pragmatic scaffold; per-task_id routing remains a follow-up. | 🟢 | session 46 (user: "show the extraction running … its steps … what are these executing of in each step … upgrade as some question for the planning and write the code") | (1) Page says "Pipeline complete" only when every in-scope row reaches `preprocessed`; (2) "Extracting PDFs · 154/156" shown while extract_gazette processing; (3) WS connects (when wired) and surfaces "Running OCR (Tesseract) — 2486/29" as a pill; (4) page works fully without WS (graceful degradation); (5) all 4 tracker files reference Session 46 / F-173. |

## Session 45 — M1 pipeline page responsiveness v2 (funnel overflow + sticky sidebar + collapsed footer)

| id | Feature | Status | Source | Acceptance |
|----|---------|--------|--------|------------|
| F-172 | **M1 pipeline page responsiveness v2 (Session 45).** Four screenshot-reported issues on `/admin/m1/pipeline`: (1) funnel chart bars overflowing card by 100× — `widthPct = (value / counts[TIERS[0].key]) * 100` divided by *ingested*; with `ingested=1, extracted=101, preprocessed=102` math produced 10,100% widths; (2) chunky native scrollbar in sidebar — earlier `* {scrollbar:none}` scoped to `html,body` only exposed sidebar's `overflow-y-auto`; (3) sidebar scrolled with page — earlier `overflow-x-hidden` on admin layout established a containing block disabling `position:sticky` on descendants; (4) collapsed sidebar footer cramped. Funnel uses `maxAcrossTiers = Math.max(1, ...TIERS.map(t => counts[t.key] ?? 0))` denominator + clamps `widthPct` to `[0,100]` + adds `overflow-hidden` + `bg-muted/30` on track parent. Sidebar gets `scrollbar-hide` on inner `<nav>` + `mx-1.5` collapsed margin + `p-1.5` collapsed bottom padding; `UserRow` rewritten — collapsed = vertical stack with Tooltip-wrapped avatar/logout, expanded = horizontal hover row, avatar gets `ring-1 ring-border/60`. Admin layout switches `overflow-x-hidden` → `overflow-x-clip` on both flex container + main column. | 🟢 | session 45 (user-shared screenshots) | (1) Funnel bars stay inside card regardless of count distribution; (2) sidebar sits still as page scrolls; (3) no native scrollbar visible in sidebar; (4) collapsed avatar + logout stacked vertically with hover tooltips; (5) `npm run build` clean. |

## Session 44 — Theme polish (view-transition animation smoothness + disable system tracking)

| id | Feature | Status | Source | Acceptance |
|----|---------|--------|--------|------------|
| F-171 | **Theme polish (Session 44).** Two unrelated theme issues. (1) View-transition reveal felt twitchy — `startViewTransition` clip-path used `ease-in-out` over 420 ms; universal `* { transition: ... }` rule competed underneath. (2) App auto-changed theme when OS flipped colour scheme. `theme-toggle.tsx` easing → `cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1)` (easeOutQuint), duration 420ms → 600ms; subtle scale (1.015→1) + opacity (0.92→1) on new layer; scale (1→0.985) + opacity (1→0.6) on old layer; flips `theme-transitioning` class on `<html>`; Sun/Moon icon transitions synced to 500 ms. `globals.css` adds GPU promotion (`will-change`, `backface-visibility`, `transform-origin`) on `::view-transition-old/new(root)` + `html.theme-transitioning *` rule suppressing universal transitions during the view-transition window. `providers.tsx` `ThemeProvider`: `defaultTheme="system"` → `"light"`, `enableSystem={false}`, `storageKey="enigmatrix-theme"`. | 🟢 | session 44 (user: "fix this issues — its automatically changing theme switching … and theme animation smoother") | (1) Toggle reveal animates smoothly ~600ms, no flicker; (2) OS auto-flips colour scheme → app theme unchanged; (3) preference persists in localStorage under `enigmatrix-theme`; (4) `setTheme` only invoked from `theme-toggle.tsx` (verified via grep). |

